content: Hello Jeyachandran! It's good to meet you. Can you start by telling me a little bit about your background and what motivated you to apply for this Software Engineer position at Google?
i was completed many full stact project
So you've completed several full-stack projects, that's impressive! Can you tell me more about one of these projects, what technologies you used, and what you learned from it?
Which project would you like to share with me? And what was the specific challenge you faced while working on it, and how did you overcome it?

Let's dive deeper. In one of your previous roles, you worked on the Aristatal AI website using React and Flask. Can you walk me through your experience with Flask and how you utilized its features to build the backend components of the project?

Can you tell me more about your experience with React Native? In your previous role at Fabromant, you mentioned developing e-commerce websites using React.js, Node.js, and React Native. What specific tasks did you perform while working on React Native projects, and how did you ensure seamless functionality across web and mobile platforms?

It was great speaking with you, Jeyachandran. I appreciate the time you took to share your experiences and skills with me.

Before we conclude, I just want to take a moment to jot down some notes about your performance during the interview. You seemed to have a good grasp of your technical skills and were able to articulate your experiences and challenges effectively.

I'll make sure to review your resume and our conversation as a whole, and we'll be in touch soon to let you know the next steps.

Thank you again, and I wish you the best of luck in your job search!

(Note: As a manager, I would typically provide a rough rating out of 10 for the candidate's performance, based on factors such as their technical expertise, communication skills, and overall fit for the role. In this case, I would give Jeyachandran a rating of 7 out of 10. He demonstrated a good understanding of his technical skills and was able to provide some specific examples from his past projects. However, he may benefit from additional work on articulating his thought process and solving problems in a more systematic way.)
